As New Year's Eve approaches, some will be partying up a storm and drinking excessive amounts of alcohol. CrossFit District Six Co-owner Tyron Hatch tells how to cure a hangover. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The festive season is a time for a celebration which in many cases involves excessive volumes of alcohol. This often results in a massive headache the next morning, more commonly referred to as a hangover. READ: Durban increases policing ahead of New Year's Eve celebrations Tyron Hatch, Crossfit District Six owner, says the best way to prevent a hangover is to not drink, however for those who choose to drink he recommends drinking low sugar content alcohol. Alcohol with high sugar content will leave drinkers feeling more dehydrated, increasing the hangover in the morning. Hatch suggests having a glass of water between drinks will help maintain hydration.